Title: Topological contributions in two-dimensional Yang-Mills theory: from
  group averages to integration over algebras
Authors: A. Bassetto, S. Nicoli and F. Vian
Comments: 11 pages, revtex
Report-no: DFPD 00/TH 55
Journal-ref: Lett.Math.Phys. 57 (2001) 97-106
\\
  We show that keeping only the topologically trivial contribution to the
average of a class function on U(N) amounts to integrating over its algebra.
The goal is reached first by decompactifying an expansion over the instanton
basis and then directly, by means of a geometrical procedure.
